In [7]:
def rgb(img):
    blue = img[0:img.shape[0]//3]
    green = img[img.shape[0]//3:img.shape[0]//3*2]
    red = img[img.shape[0]//3*2:img.shape[0]//3*3]
    return (red,green,blue)

In [8]:
def cutting(image, h=0.1, l=0.05):
        image=image[int(image.shape[0]*h):int(image.shape[0]*(1-h)),int(image.shape[1]*l):int(image.shape[1]*(1-l))]
        return image
In [9]:
def correlation (img1, img2):
    max_correlation=0
    for row in range(-15,16):
        for col in range(-15,16):
            img3=np.roll(img2,(row,col), axis=(0,1))           
            correlation = (skimage.img_as_float(img3)*skimage.img_as_float(img1)).sum()
            if correlation > max_correlation:
                max_correlation=correlation.copy()
                best_row = row
                best_col = col
    return (best_row, best_col)
In [10]:
def func(r,g,b):
    b_shift = correlation(g,b)
    new_b = np.roll(b,b_shift, axis = (0,1))
    r_shift = correlation(g,r)
    new_r = np.roll(r,r_shift,axis=(0,1))
    return np.dstack((new_r,g,new_b))

def show_color_img(img):
    return show(func(cutting(rgb(img)[0]),cutting(rgb(img)[1]),cutting(rgb(img)[2])))
